deck: Ruler of Hell.
description:
Origin

Belia is the daughter of the Dark One. He put her in Hell, where she rules over the dead.

Major Story Arcs

Inferno: Age of Darkness

Belia's father, the Dark One, asks Belia to take his side in the coming war. She initially declines, but hatches a plan to double-cross them. At an informal dinner, Belia's stepmother the Dark Queen, show Belia the powerful gem Cyclops' Eye. Belia sends her mercenary Mercy Dante and their prisoner Masumi, to steal the gem. The Dark Queen catches them in the act and has secretly replaced the gem with a bomb. Mercy and Masumi narrowly escape.

Inferno: Rings of Hell

Punished by her father and stepmother the Dark Queen for betraying them, Belia and Mercy Dante are put through Hell, literally. If they survive the nine rings of Hell, they would be free. Mercy and Belia fight valiantly and, to the surprise of them both, they manage to survive the experience. Returning to London, Belia confronts the Dark Queen, vowing to destroy everything the Dark Queen has build up. Answering her, the Dark Queen kills Belia by shooting her.

God of Destruction
Beerus the Destroyer
deck: Beerus is the ancient God of Destruction of the 7th Universe, tasked with maintaining universal balance through destruction. He is the brother to Champa, and a feared being throughout the universe.
description:
Dragon Ball Z: Battle of Gods

Beerus appears in the movie, Dragon ball Z: Battle of Gods, and is the main antagonist of the film. His job is to maintain balance in the 7th universe where Goku and the rest of the Z Fighters reside.

Personality

At times well mannered and occasionally courteous, Beerus has exhibited a deadly short temper, easily angered if things don't go his way. He is shown to destroy planets for petty reasons such as losing in a game of hide and seek, or if deserts aren't shared with him. Though not necessarily evil (destruction is simply his duty, after all), he isn't above making threatening comments when annoyed. He is obsessed with food and other delicacies, with food being one of the reasons he has chosen to spare the earth.

Biography

Beerus is feared throughout the universe, even by the Gods of Creation/Kais. He usually sleeps for many years and when he awakens he destroys. Since he does not act on orders received from the Supreme Kai's, he would destroy seemingly any world without a second thought. It's implied he also destroys more than what is needed since Toriyama said when the worlds balance begins to crumble, the 4 regular Kai's have to help out the Supreme Kais in creation as well. Once every 1,000 years, the Supreme Kais and Gods of Destruction go to each others realms and hold a coordination meeting. During one of these meetings, Beerus sealed away old Kai in the Z Sword after an argument took place among them.

Beerus at one time mentioned that he came to Earth before and rendered the Dinosaurs extinct since they did not like him. Some 39 years before the events of Battle of Gods, the Prophecy Fish foretold that a strong opponent would appear before him, which was the Super Saiyan God. Beerus recalls having a dream where he fought a Super Saiyan god and that's when he approached the Prophecy Fish about the situation. This sparks a visit to king Kai's place to meet Goku and see if he knew who the Super Saiyan God was. After defeating Goku in his super Saiyan 3 form and the other Z Fighters on Earth, Goku returns to summon Shenron and ask him about legend of Saiyan God. Once the ritual of making the Super Saiyan God was complete, Goku fought somewhat evenly with Beerus and later absorbs the godly transformation's powers into himself. Goku struggled to hold back Beerus energy sphere in space and after transforming into the Super Saiyan God again, Goku erases the energy ball from existence.

Powers & Abilities

Although Goku had gained the Super Saiyan God transformation, Beerus proved too much for him to handle in the end, forcing Goku to give up the battle. Beerus defeated Super Saiyan 3 Goku, an enraged Super Saiyan 2 Vegeta, Piccolo, Super Gotenks, Android 18, Tien and Mystic Gohan with relative ease. Such warriors had 5 years of training after the Buu Saga, but even this was not near enough to challenge Beerus' power. Goku himself feared that if he fused with Vegeta he wouldn't be able to overcome the God of Destruction.

Beerus power was further showcased in Dragon Ball Super, in which the battle between the Destroyer and Super Saiyan God Goku threatened to destroy the universe do to their collective output. Later, Whis compared Goku and Vegeta (who just begun training under Whis) to a small tree in comparison to Beerus, who was a castle. It isn't hard to believe more damage could have been done to the universe had Beerus truly held nothing back against the Saiyan. Even a mostly playful fight between Beerus and fellow God/Twin Brother Champa resulted in many planets and moons being destroyed, with both implying they are willing to destroy the universe to best the other before being incapacitated by their respective attendants.

Beerus is also a knowledgeable master martial artist, more so than even Goku and Vegeta, to the point where he defeated both and the combined might of the Z-Fighters with mere pressure points. He has made use of his combat skills and godly abilities in combat many times, even creating versatile combinations mid battle, such as creating clones of himself to attack Goku from all angles, infusing Goku's body with Ki to create an explosion like effect, and using advanced forms of Ki manipulation to catch and redirect enemy attacks as he did so against an alien warrior on another planet. Perhaps his best demonstration of power so far was containing and neutralizing an ultra dense Ki sphere created by the clashing of his and Goku's attacks, which was stated to be capable of destroying the universe if it exploded.

deck: The last Type-V Mutant alive. Caerula actions have played a vital role in shaping the history of Battle Angel Alita.
description:
Origin

Creation

Personality

Major Story Arcs

Powers & Abilities

Caerula has displayed that she is a formidable opponent even against cybernetic opponents such as Alita despite herself being flesh and blood. Her knowledge and mastery's of varying combat fields coupled the abilities granted to her for being a Type-V Mutant make her virtually unmatched.

Immortal: As a type-v mutant she has displayed some semblance of immortality. She's lived for over 700 years and hasn't aged a day. She however can be injured and killed much in the same fashion a normal human would such a decapitation and drowning.

Healing: Her healing factor is quite high. Having stayed in a tomb for roughly forty years after sustaining injuries that would have killed a normal human. Her body still lived on despite it appearing as a shriveled corpse when it was found. When drinking fresh human blood, her healing factor is significantly increased. Such as her arm regrowing which had previously been torn off or when her stomach was fully restored after being impaled by Alita's Damascus Arm Blades.

Danger Sense: The "Neural Pulse Flow" allows Caerula to see the presence and trajectory of everything within her surroundings. Be it bullet trajectories, enemies, and even miniscule details such as "seeing a mouses movement under shadow". She can even see invisible opponents. This nullifies any speed advantage her opponent would have.

Super Strength, Agility, & Speed: She has displayed degree of super strength, agility, and speed. A feat of strength would be her catching a thrown SUV with her sword and hurling it back at her opponent. A feat of speed would be her traveling to Alita from twenty feet away and punching her core before Alita could even react. A feat of agility would be her dodging bullets even before she could see the "neural pulse flow".

Swordsmanship, Marksmanship, Weapon Mastery, & Unarmed Combat: With all the combat experience Caerula has acquired in the course of 700 years, it in addition to her sense of the "Neural Pulse Flow" has granted her too see 100 moves ahead while in combat. She has at the very least mastered 48 schools & 128 divisions of Kung Fu.

Her display with her duel jian (Swords) "Earthlight" & "Moonlight" is rather impressive. With but the slightest twist of her wrist she can effectively bend these blades at will. Such instances would be bending one around a sword in it's path, deliberately avoiding a death blow to the head, or destroying an SUV's engine. These blades have a magnetic property which allows her to use iron fillings which she uses to act as a wipe. She can even create minor spark strong enough to trigger a bullet to fire.

She has displayed the use of other tools such as acupuncture needle hidden in one of her Jian. Her Piau daggers which she can toss dozens in less then a second. And the use of guns which she incorporates in her more deadly moves.
name: Caerula Sanguis
